20
00:01:11,433 --> 00:01:15,199
Each case contains twenty-four tins.

21
00:01:15,233 --> 00:01:17,135
We need to calculate how many

22
00:01:17,235 --> 00:01:19,965
tins the supermarket receives altogether.

23
00:01:20,033 --> 00:01:23,068
Since we have two hundred and thirty-five groups of

24
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:27,063
twenty-four, our strategy is multiplication. We need to calculate

25
00:01:27,163 --> 00:01:30,382
two hundred and thirty-five multiplied by twenty-four.

26
00:01:31,933 --> 00:01:35,758
There are several ways to perform this calculation. You should

27
00:01:35,858 --> 00:01:39,367
use the method you are most comfortable with. Let's start

28
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:42,595
with the Grid Method, also known as the Box Method.

29
00:01:42,666 --> 00:01:45,017
We break two hundred and thirty-five

30
00:01:45,117 --> 00:01:47,399
into two hundred, thirty, and five.

31
00:01:47,466 --> 00:01:51,232
We break twenty-four into twenty and four.

32
00:01:51,266 --> 00:01:57,775
Now we multiply each part. Two hundred times twenty is four thousand.

33
00:01:57,866 --> 00:02:01,632
Thirty times twenty is six hundred.

34
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:05,432
Five times twenty is one hundred.

35
00:02:05,466 --> 00:02:09,729
Then we multiply by four: Two hundred times four is eight hundred.

36
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:14,062
Thirty times four is one hundred and twenty.

37
00:02:14,133 --> 00:02:17,272
Five times four is twenty.

38
00:02:17,333 --> 00:02:21,322
Finally, we add all these answers together: Four thousand plus

39
00:02:21,422 --> 00:02:25,279
six hundred plus one hundred is four thousand seven hundred.

40
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:28,663
Eight hundred plus one hundred and twenty

41
00:02:28,763 --> 00:02:31,842
plus twenty is nine hundred and forty.

42
00:02:31,933 --> 00:02:36,156
Adding four thousand seven hundred and nine hundred and forty gives

43
00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:39,382
us a total of five thousand six hundred and forty.

44
00:02:40,966 --> 00:02:43,635
Now let's look at the Column Method.

45
00:02:46,433 --> 00:02:51,165
First, we multiply two hundred and thirty-five by four.

46
00:02:51,233 --> 00:02:55,495
Four times five is twenty, so write the zero and carry the two.

47
00:02:55,566 --> 00:02:59,161
Four times three is twelve, plus the carried two

48
00:02:59,261 --> 00:03:02,702
is fourteen. Write the four and carry the one.

49
00:03:02,766 --> 00:03:05,927
Four times two is eight, plus the one is

50
00:03:06,027 --> 00:03:09,432
nine. This gives us nine hundred and forty.

51
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:13,155
Next, we multiply by the twenty. We start

52
00:03:13,255 --> 00:03:16,635
by placing a zero in the units column.

53
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:22,555
Then, two times five is ten; write zero, carry one.

54
00:03:22,633 --> 00:03:27,365
Two times three is six, plus one is seven.

55
00:03:27,633 --> 00:03:32,365
Two times two is four. This gives us four thousand seven hundred.

56
00:03:32,433 --> 00:03:36,740
Finally, we add nine hundred and forty and four thousand seven

57
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:41,005
hundred together to get five thousand six hundred and forty.

58
00:03:43,433 --> 00:03:46,468
Both methods give us the same result:

59
00:03:46,568 --> 00:03:49,942
five thousand six hundred and forty tins.

